The paper proposes a framework for learning planning domains, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework involves updating the perception function, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The framework also involves adapting the transition function, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with exogenous events, which is a common topic in planning (cs.PL).
